### CodeCraftHub REST API Test File
### Use with VS Code REST Client Extension (https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=humao.rest-client)

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api

### 1. Get all courses
GET {{baseUrl}}/courses

### 2. Create a new course - JavaScript
POST {{baseUrl}}/courses
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "JavaScript Basics",
  "description": "Learn the fundamentals of JavaScript including variables, functions, and event handling",
  "completionDate": "2026-06-30",
  "status": "Not Started"
}

### 3. Create a new course - React
POST {{baseUrl}}/courses
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "React Fundamentals",
  "description": "Build dynamic user interfaces with React, components, props, and state",
  "completionDate": "2026-07-31",
  "status": "Not Started"
}

### 4. Create a new course - Node.js
POST {{baseUrl}}/courses
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Node.js & Express",
  "description": "Build backend applications with Node.js and Express framework",
  "completionDate": "2026-08-15",
  "status": "In Progress"
}

### 5. Get a specific course (ID: 1)
GET {{baseUrl}}/courses/1

### 6. Get a specific course (ID: 2)
GET {{baseUrl}}/courses/2

### 7. Update course status to In Progress (ID: 1)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/courses/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "In Progress"
}

### 8. Update course status to Completed (ID: 3)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/courses/3
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "Completed"
}

### 9. Update multiple fields (ID: 2)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/courses/2
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "In Progress",
  "completionDate": "2026-07-15",
  "description": "Build interactive UIs with React, hooks, context API, and state management"
}

### 10. Delete a course (ID: 3)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/courses/3

### 11. Get all courses again to verify changes
GET {{baseUrl}}/courses

### Test: Try to get non-existent course (should return 404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/courses/999

### Test: Try to update non-existent course (should return 404)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/courses/999
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "Completed"
}

### Test: Try to delete non-existent course (should return 404)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/courses/999

### Test: Invalid status value (should return 400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/courses
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Invalid Course",
  "description": "This course has an invalid status",
  "completionDate": "2026-06-30",
  "status": "Invalid Status"
}

### Test: Missing required fields (should return 400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/courses
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Incomplete Course"
}
